@node "And finally..." "And finally..."

Here are some things I'd like to do in future volumes:

*   a GUI. Yes, I mentioned this before, but I've yet to explore the
    alternatives. VARexx was a nice little program, but it hasn't been
    developed for some time. There is supposed to be an MUI equivalent,
    and I could use that provided MUI-phobes don't start complaining.

*   OK, so I still haven't got round to it, but a way of linking
    TurboCalc to the bar (see volume one) and the pie chart generation
    scripts would make them a little less cumbersome. I'd also like to
    add the facility to add labels to them.

*   I've been working on a Thumbnails script which allows the
    combination of multiple documents onto one page. It's still far from
    complete and makes things look a bit of a mess at the moment, but
    it's getting there.

*   Animation. Maybe.

...and if you have any further suggestions, get in contact with me.

    If you feel the urge to contact me, my E-Mail address is:
odin@dcs.qmw.ac.uk. This address may well disappear after the 31st July
if I decide to get a job rather than hang around for PostGraduate study.
I've still yet to make a decision on that one... Either way, check out
http://www.qmw.ac.uk/~amiga/members.html. My new E-Mail address will
appear there should it change. For any non-netsurfers, I can be
snail-mailed at 178 Carterhatch Road, Enfield, Middlesex, EN3 5LY, England.

    See you in the next volume!

@endnode
